  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package was signed at the conclusion of the initial assessment cycle; however, one supplementary validation result was appended post-signing following a late experimental campaign, without triggering a re-sign of the package. The evidenceTimestamp on that result therefore falls strictly after the signatureTimestamp, constituting a W-CON-03 consistency defect.",
